"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1060582","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-02-20","<p>The Northern Ireland (Executive Formation and Exercise of Functions) Act 2018 and associated guidance gives greater certainty to enable NI Departments to continue to take decisions in Northern Ireland in the public interest. The redetermination of the planning application is a devolved matter and falls to the Department for Infrastructure. As such, I would encourage you to contact the Northern Ireland Department for Infrastructure for further information.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","220822 ; 221593","2019-02-20T16:18:46.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1060582/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1060582/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1060582/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-02-13","Electricity Interconnectors: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what the timeframe is for the redetermination of the planning application for the Tyrone-Cavan interconnector.","false","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison","220821"
